Consider the following reactions (unbalanced).<br><br>$$Zn + Hot\,conc.\,{H_2}S{O_4}\mathrel{\mathop{\kern0pt\longrightarrow}
\limits_{}} G + R + X$$<br><br>$$Zn + conc.\,NaOH\mathrel{\mathop{\kern0pt\longrightarrow}
\limits_{}} T + Q$$<br><br>$$G + {H_2}S + N{H_4}OH\mathrel{\mathop{\kern0pt\longrightarrow}
\limits_{}} Z\,(a\,precipitate) + X + Y$$<br><br>Choose the correct option(s).

en.explanation:
When Zn react with hot conc. H<sub>2</sub>SO<sub>4</sub> then SO<sub>2</sub> is released and ZnSO<sub>4</sub> is obtained.<br><br> <picture><source media="(max-width: 320px)" srcset="https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kt7tcl3g/7573fa86-be26-4f6c-a0cb-b3ae6fd575ac/5d9a40c0-0e9c-11ec-87ef-035aec66293c/file-1kt7tcl3h-320w.jpeg"><source media="(max-width: 500px)" srcset="https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kt7tcl3g/7573fa86-be26-4f6c-a0cb-b3ae6fd575ac/5d9a40c0-0e9c-11ec-87ef-035aec66293c/file-1kt7tcl3h-500w.jpeg"><source media="(max-width: 680px)" srcset="https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kt7tcl3g/7573fa86-be26-4f6c-a0cb-b3ae6fd575ac/5d9a40c0-0e9c-11ec-87ef-035aec66293c/file-1kt7tcl3h-680w.jpeg"><source media="(max-width: 860px)" srcset="https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kt7tcl3g/7573fa86-be26-4f6c-a0cb-b3ae6fd575ac/5d9a40c0-0e9c-11ec-87ef-035aec66293c/file-1kt7tcl3h-860w.jpeg"><source media="(max-width: 1040px)" srcset="https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kt7tcl3g/7573fa86-be26-4f6c-a0cb-b3ae6fd575ac/5d9a40c0-0e9c-11ec-87ef-035aec66293c/file-1kt7tcl3h-1040w.jpeg"><source media="(max-width: 1220px)" srcset="https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kt7tcl3g/7573fa86-be26-4f6c-a0cb-b3ae6fd575ac/5d9a40c0-0e9c-11ec-87ef-035aec66293c/file-1kt7tcl3h-1220w.jpeg"><source media="(max-width: 1400px)" srcset="https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kt7tcl3g/7573fa86-be26-4f6c-a0cb-b3ae6fd575ac/5d9a40c0-0e9c-11ec-87ef-035aec66293c/file-1kt7tcl3h-1400w.jpeg"><img src="https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kt7tcl3g/7573fa86-be26-4f6c-a0cb-b3ae6fd575ac/5d9a40c0-0e9c-11ec-87ef-035aec66293c/file-1kt7tcl3h.jpeg" style="max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;" loading="lazy" alt="JEE Advanced 2019 Paper 2 Offline Chemistry - p-Block Elements Question 61 English Explanation 1"></picture> <br><br>R(SO<sub>2</sub>) molecule is V-shaped<br><br> <img src="https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kt7td81t/b7b85f02-750e-42b3-b7b8-e21b012fc9f6/6f559710-0e9c-11ec-87ef-035aec66293c/file-1kt7td81u.jpeg" style="max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;" loading="lazy" alt="JEE Advanced 2019 Paper 2 Offline Chemistry - p-Block Elements Question 61 English Explanation 2"> <br><br>Thus, option (b) is correct.<br><br>When Zn is react with conc. NaOH then H<sub>2</sub> gas is evolved and Na<sub>2</sub>ZnO<sub>2</sub> is obtained.<br><br>$$Zn + 2NaOH(conc.)\mathrel{\mathop{\kern0pt\longrightarrow}
\limits_{}} \mathop {N{a_2}Zn{O_2}}\limits_{(T)}  + \mathop {{H_2}}\limits_{(Q)}  \uparrow $$<br><br>In ground state, H$$-$$H (Q)<br><br>(bond order = 1)<br><br>Thus, option (c) is correct.<br><br>The oxidation state of Zn in T(Na<sub>2</sub>ZnO<sub>2</sub>) is +2<br><br>Thus, option (a) is incorrect.<br><br>$$\mathop {ZnS{O_4}}\limits_{(G)}  + {H_2}S + N{H_4}OH\mathrel{\mathop{\kern0pt\longrightarrow}
\limits_{}} \mathop {ZnS}\limits_{(Z)}  \downarrow  + \mathop {2{H_2}O}\limits_{(X)}  + \mathop {{{(N{H_4})}_2}S{O_4}}\limits_{(Y)} $$<br><br>ZnS (Z) compound is dirty white coloured.<br><br>Thus, option (d) is correct.

hi.explanation:
जब Zn गर्म सांद्र H<sub>2</sub>SO<sub>4</sub> के साथ अभिक्रिया करता है तो SO<sub>2</sub> मुक्त होती है और ZnSO<sub>4</sub> प्राप्त होता है।<br><br> <picture><source media="(max-width: 320px)" srcset="https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kt7tcl3g/7573fa86-be26-4f6c-a0cb-b3ae6fd575ac/5d9a40c0-0e9c-11ec-87ef-035aec66293c/file-1kt7tcl3h-320w.jpeg"><source media="(max-width: 500px)" srcset="https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kt7tcl3g/7573fa86-be26-4f6c-a0cb-b3ae6fd575ac/5d9a40c0-0e9c-11ec-87ef-035aec66293c/file-1kt7tcl3h-500w.jpeg"><source media="(max-width: 680px)" srcset="https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kt7tcl3g/7573fa86-be26-4f6c-a0cb-b3ae6fd575ac/5d9a40c0-0e9c-11ec-87ef-035aec66293c/file-1kt7tcl3h-680w.jpeg"><source media="(max-width: 860px)" srcset="https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kt7tcl3g/7573fa86-be26-4f6c-a0cb-b3ae6fd575ac/5d9a40c0-0e9c-11ec-87ef-035aec66293c/file-1kt7tcl3h-860w.jpeg"><source media="(max-width: 1040px)" srcset="https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kt7tcl3g/7573fa86-be26-4f6c-a0cb-b3ae6fd575ac/5d9a40c0-0e9c-11ec-87ef-035aec66293c/file-1kt7tcl3h-1040w.jpeg"><source media="(max-width: 1220px)" srcset="https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kt7tcl3g/7573fa86-be26-4f6c-a0cb-b3ae6fd575ac/5d9a40c0-0e9c-11ec-87ef-035aec66293c/file-1kt7tcl3h-1220w.jpeg"><source media="(max-width: 1400px)" srcset="https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kt7tcl3g/7573fa86-be26-4f6c-a0cb-b3ae6fd575ac/5d9a40c0-0e9c-11ec-87ef-035aec66293c/file-1kt7tcl3h-1400w.jpeg"><img src="https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kt7tcl3g/7573fa86-be26-4f6c-a0cb-b3ae6fd575ac/5d9a40c0-0e9c-11ec-87ef-035aec66293c/file-1kt7tcl3h.jpeg" style="max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;" loading="lazy" alt="JEE Advanced 2019 Paper 2 Offline Chemistry - p-Block Elements Question 61 Hindi Explanation 1"></picture> <br><br>R(SO<sub>2</sub>) अणु V-आकार का है<br><br> <img src="https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1kt7td81t/b7b85f02-750e-42b3-b7b8-e21b012fc9f6/6f559710-0e9c-11ec-87ef-035aec66293c/file-1kt7td81u.jpeg" style="max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;" loading="lazy" alt="JEE Advanced 2019 Paper 2 Offline Chemistry - p-Block Elements Question 61 Hindi Explanation 2"> <br><br>इस प्रकार, विकल्प (b) सही है।<br><br>जब Zn सांद्र NaOH के साथ अभिक्रिया करता है तो H<sub>2</sub> गैस मुक्त होती है और Na<sub>2</sub>ZnO<sub>2</sub> प्राप्त होता है।<br><br>$$Zn + 2NaOH(conc.)\mathrel{\mathop{\kern0pt\longrightarrow}
\limits_{}} \mathop {N{a_2}Zn{O_2}}\limits_{(T)}  + \mathop {{H_2}}\limits_{(Q)}  \uparrow $$<br><br>मूल अवस्था में, H$$-$$H (Q)<br><br>(बंध कोटि = 1)<br><br>इस प्रकार, विकल्प (c) सही है।<br><br>T(Na<sub>2</sub>ZnO<sub>2</sub>) में Zn की ऑक्सीकरण अवस्था +2 है<br><br>इस प्रकार, विकल्प (a) गलत है।<br><br>$$\mathop {ZnS{O_4}}\limits_{(G)}  + {H_2}S + N{H_4}OH\mathrel{\mathop{\kern0pt\longrightarrow}
\limits_{}} \mathop {ZnS}\limits_{(Z)}  \downarrow  + \mathop {2{H_2}O}\limits_{(X)}  + \mathop {{{(N{H_4})}_2}S{O_4}}\limits_{(Y)} $$<br><br>ZnS (Z) यौगिक गंदे सफेद रंग का होता है।<br><br>इस प्रकार, विकल्प (d) सही है।
